      "span_text": "However, the type of required reasoning is not always purely logical (true or false, 1 or 0) but can also be probabilistic (the degree of certainty or probability that an event will happen, represented by a value between 0 and 1). Bayesian networks (BNs) have been chosen by many previous researchers as models for managing probabilistic reasoning in ontologies [CITATION_1] ."
